      <h1 class="title">Using Capybara and Rspec assertions in Page Objects</h1>
      <h2 class="subtitle">Writing well encapsulated tests in Rails with the Page Object pattern</h2>
    </header>

    <section>
      <p>On my Rails project, I am using RSpec and Capybara to write functional tests.<br />
I did not want to specify any HTML elements in my Capybara feature files, since that makes the 
feature files brittle to HTML / CSS changes. It also violates the DRY principle and basic code hygiene.</p>

<p>Read the full blog on my older blog site here:
<a href="http://techie-notebook.blogspot.com/2014/01/using-capybara-and-rspec-assertions-in.html">Using Capybara and Rspec assertions in Page Objects</a></p>

      
